<subSubSection lastPageId="60" lastPageNumber="61" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,1880,2015]" box="[151,558,1880,1907]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,1880,1907]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,1880,2015]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1916,1943]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Distribution.</emphasis>
Thus far only recorded from Britain. 
<collectingCountry box="[794,893,1917,1943]" name="Portugal" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: one province (Beira Litoral), first record from continental Europe!
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,1880,2015]" lastBlockId="60.[151,1437,153,287]" lastPageId="60" lastPageNumber="61" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1989,2015]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Ecology.</emphasis>
The only Portuguese specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chandler &amp; Negrobov" authorityYear="2008" box="[693,813,1989,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Xanthochlorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silaceus">
<emphasis box="[693,813,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">X. silaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were recorded from a pine forest with 
<taxonomicName box="[1242,1360,1989,2015]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1242,1320,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Acacia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[151,258,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[1371,1436,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Arbutus</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[190,258,153,179]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Arbutus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="unedo">unedo</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[272,418,153,179]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[272,366,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Quercus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P.Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[471,650,153,179]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativa">
<emphasis box="[471,650,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Castanea sativa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and a botanical garden with artificial ponds and fountains. Its ecology is largely unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,153,287]" box="[199,456,224,251]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,224,251]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
2.3 (rare).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,153,287]" box="[199,511,260,287]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,260,287]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Activity period.</emphasis>
June–July.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,948,332,360]" box="[151,948,332,360]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
150.? 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wiedemann, 1817) (Xanthochlorinae)" authorityName="Xanthochlorinae" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[227,948,332,360]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Xanthochlorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenellus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,737,332,359]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,496,332,359]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Xanthochlorus tenellus</emphasis>
(Wiedemann, 1817)
</emphasis>
(Xanthochlorinae)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,404,575]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,404,431]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe, but rather uncertain since the discovery of two new 
<taxonomicName box="[986,1238,405,431]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[986,1151,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Xanthochlorus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in Britain (
<bibRefCitation author="Chandler, P. J. &amp; Negrobov, O. P." pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="29 - 40" refId="ref32436" refString="Chandler, P. J. &amp; Negrobov, O. P. (2008) The British species of Xanthochlorus Loew, 1857 (Diptera, Dolichopodidae), with description of two new species. Dipterists Digest, 15, 29 - 40." type="journal article" year="2008">Chandler &amp; Negrobov 2008</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[429,528,441,467]" name="Portugal" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: Beira Alta (
<bibRefCitation author="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M." box="[667,921,440,467]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="125 - 137" refId="ref33294" refString="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M. (2015) Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from the Iberian Peninsula, with description of three new species. Zootaxa, 3964 (1), 125 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3964.1.9" type="journal article" year="2015">Naglis &amp; Barták 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,404,575]" box="[199,1138,477,503]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,477,503]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Ecology.</emphasis>
Mainly recorded from open, rather dry deciduous forests and forest edges.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,404,575]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,513,539]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M." box="[322,586,512,539]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="125 - 137" refId="ref33294" refString="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M. (2015) Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from the Iberian Peninsula, with description of three new species. Zootaxa, 3964 (1), 125 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3964.1.9" type="journal article" year="2015">Naglis &amp; Barták (2015)</bibRefCitation>
listed only one female specimen, which we treat here as uncertain considering the slight and often indecisive colour differences between females of related species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,952,656,684]" box="[151,952,656,684]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName box="[151,356,656,683]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Pelastoneurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,356,656,683]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,316,656,683]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Pelastoneurus</emphasis>
sp.
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[371,553,657,684]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Dolichopodinae">Dolichopodinae</taxonomicName>
)— 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[589,952,656,683]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">new to the Palaearctic Region!</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,729,828]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,729,755]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Remarks.</emphasis>
One female specimen was collected on 
<date box="[723,869,729,755]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" value="2014-07-13">
13 July 
<quantity box="[813,869,729,755]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.11556" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" unit="in" value="2014.0">2014</quantity>
</date>
in Castro Marim (district 
<collectingRegion box="[1167,1220,729,755]" country="Portugal" name="Faro" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Faro</collectingRegion>
) in the province of Algarve. It features all characteristics of this primarily tropical genus that is known from all zoogeographical realms except for the Palaearctic and Afrotropics (Yang 
<emphasis box="[698,754,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">et al.</emphasis>
2016).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
